name: Air-Fried Taco Dogs
author: Buckwheat Queen
summary: Hot dogs cooked in an air fryer inside their buns, then topped with taco fixings, will redefine Taco Tuesday. The air fryer renders the hot dogs crispy on the outside and juicy on the inside.
directions: Preheat an air fryer to 390 degrees F (200 degrees C)
Make sure the air fryer is at temperature for at least 4 minutes
Cut 5 slits into each hot dog
Evenly rub 1/2 teaspoon   over each hot dog
Cook hot dogs in the air fryer basket for 5 minutes
Place hot dogs in buns and return to the basket
Cook until buns are toasted and hot dogs are crisp, about 4 minutes more
Top hot dogs with equal amounts of guacamole, salsa, and jalapenos
